{
  "text": "It is now well-known that chemotherapy has severe neurotoxic side effects that can persist long after treatment completion [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Additionally, although the neurotoxic effects of radiation and surgery are less studied, the evidence for shortand long-term neurotoxic side effects from these treatment modalities is compelling [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . Less well-established are the neurotoxic symptoms associated with cancer itself, present prior to commencement of any cancer treatment. Nevertheless, accumulating evidence indicates that a significant number of treatment-naïve breast cancer patients already suffer from mild cognitive deficits, fatigue, and (breast) pain [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] .",
  "correct_citation": {
